	   <tr><td colspan=2>Ok, in Velious and Kunark the hate lists work diffrently than the rest of the world. In the "old world" you kill something it dies good. In Kunark/Velious if you heal, buff, or help out some one killing a mob in any way then you have just put yourself on the hate list of any one on that faction. You kill/help kill/buff some one killing a giant and all giants will hate you. You may not notice it at first but after a while it builds up high enough that you start takeing faction hits, that is when it is time to zone/relog to clear you hate lists. I don't think that they have changed this in the old world but they may have. Now it's time to go rant about mages needing mana regen again, check in later, maybe.<br>&nbsp;<br>Great spirits encounter violent opposition from mediocre minds and yes I know I can't spell too</td></tr>
